{"sections":[],"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A native ad is a type of paid promotion that seamlessly integrates into its surrounding content, mirroring the look and feel of the platform it appears on. Designed to blend in rather than disrupt, native ads aim to deliver a more organic and engaging advertising experience for users."}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.cloudx.CloudXCore\/documentation\/CloudXCore"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Create-and-load-a-CloudXNativeAdView","text":"Create and load a CloudXNativeAdView","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The initial step in integrating native ads involves incorporating a "},{"code":"CloudXNativeAdView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" object into your view hierarchy, as native ads are presented within these objects."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Configure","anchor":"Configure"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a "},{"code":"CloudXNativeAdView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" object by using "},{"code":"CloudX\/createNativeAd(placement:viewController:delegate:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" method with an placement ID. It returns a view object. Call its "},{"code":"CloudXAd\/load()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" method to load assets for native ad.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In order to load and display ads you need,"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"viewController:","type":"text"}]},{"text":" This view controller is used to present an overlay when the ad is clicked. It should normally be set to the view controller that contains the ","type":"text"},{"code":"CloudXNativeAdView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlin